MINONK WIND, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Minonk Wind, LLC ("MWF") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a wind generating facility located in Woodford County and Livingston County, Illinois within the Commonwealth Edison Company ("ComEd") Zone of the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule sets forth MWF's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service. This Rate Schedule shall be effective on June 1, 2019. REVENUE REQUIREMENT: Total Revenue Requirement: MWF's Total Annual Revenue Requirement shall be calculated as follows: Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $744,000.01 Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $62,000.00 (based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)
